> ### Name: format_pvalue
> ### Title: Format P-Values for Display
> ### Aliases: format_pvalue
> 
> ### ** Examples
> 
> # Basic usage
> format_pvalue(0.05)
[1] "= .0500"
> format_pvalue(0.0001)
[1] "= .0001"
> 
> # More rounding
> format_pvalue(0.0001,digits=2)
[1] "< .01"
> 
> # Vector input
> format_pvalue(c(0.05, 0.001, 0.00001, 0.99))
[1] "= .0500" "= .0010" "< .0001" "= .9900"
> 
> # With p prefix
> format_pvalue(0.05, include_p = TRUE)
[1] "p = .0500"
> 
